2026 Regular Session ENROLLED
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 135
BY SENATOR KLEINPETER
A RESOLUTION
To express the sincere condolences of the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana upon the
death of Kathleen "Kathy" Sessums and to honor her life, legacy, and extraordinary
contributions to the state of Louisiana.
WHEREAS, it is with deep sorrow that the members of the Senate of the Legislature
of Louisiana have learned of the passing of Kathleen "Kathy" Sessums on April 22, 2026,
at the age of sixty-eight, following a long and courageous battle with cancer; and
WHEREAS, Kathy Sessums was born on August 4, 1957, and raised in Shreveport,
Louisiana, where she began a life defined by dedication, resilience, and compassion; and
WHEREAS, at the young age of thirteen, she met the love of her life, John Thomas
Sessums, and their enduring bond led to their marriage in 1974 that spanned fifty-two years;
serving as a testament to love, commitment, and partnership; and
WHEREAS, together they built a strong and loving family, welcoming twin sons and
creating a home centered on devotion, support, and shared joy; and
WHEREAS, Kathy Sessums was a devoted wife, mother, and "Mimi", whose
greatest happiness was found spending time with her children, grandchildren, beloved dogs,
and the many friends who she considered family; and
WHEREAS, whether enjoying weekends in Florida or on the river, she cherished
time on the water surrounded by loved ones, creating lasting memories that will be treasured
for generations; and
WHEREAS, Kathy Sessums will be remembered for her strength, intelligence,
warmth, and the deep and abiding love she extended to all who knew her; and
WHEREAS, her professional life was marked by an extraordinary forty-six year
career in public service with the state of Louisiana, beginning in 1978, during which she
played a pivotal role in transforming state government information systems; and
WHEREAS, starting in a clerical position, her exceptional abilities were quickly
recognized as she advanced through determination and hard work to become an agency
