accountant within the Department of Health and Human Resources, now known as the
Louisiana Department of Health; and
WHEREAS, throughout her career, she assumed numerous leadership roles and
responsibilities, demonstrating unmatched analytical reasoning and a remarkable
near-photographic memory that distinguished her among her peers; and
WHEREAS, Kathy led the development of the state's first cost allocation system at
the Louisiana Department of Health, establishing a critical foundation that continues to guide
statewide financial operations and resource management; and
WHEREAS, her expertise and vision culminated in her appointment as director of
Louisiana's Enterprise Resource Planning system, LaGov, where she oversaw the
implementation of a comprehensive, statewide system integrating accounting, finance,
budgeting, procurement, payroll, inventory, capital projects, travel, training, and grant
services; and
WHEREAS, throughout Kathy's leadership, LaGov replaced outdated and siloed
systems, modernized state operations, and generated millions of dollars in taxpayer savings,
becoming an essential component of Louisiana's governmental infrastructure; and
WHEREAS, Kathy Sessums worked tirelessly with agencies across the state to unify
systems and improve efficiency, leaving an indelible mark on the operations of state
government and the lives of Louisiana's citizens; and
WHEREAS, her dedication, mentorship, and leadership profoundly influenced
colleagues and employees, many of whom benefited from her guidance and unwavering
commitment to excellence; and
WHEREAS, in recognition of her distinguished service, she was awarded the
"Charles E. Dunbar, Jr. Career Civil Service Award" in 2022, the highest honor bestowed
upon classified state employees, a testament to her outstanding contributions to the people
of Louisiana; and
WHEREAS, she is survived by her beloved husband, John Thomas Sessums; her
sons, Brady Sessums and his wife Cinclare Sessums, and Casey Sessums and his wife
Rebecca Sessums; and her cherished grandchildren, Elizabeth Sessums, John Brady Sessums
Jr., "JB", Marcelle Sessums, and Thomas Sessums; and
